parameter.name: /basic/protocol
parameter.description: Specifies the interface protocol for information exchange with connected initiators and targets

parameter.name: /basic/BUSWIDTH
parameter.description: Specifies the internal data path width of the fabric. All external accesses will be routed internally after converting to the <BUSWIDTH>

parameter.name: /basic/arbitration_scheme
parameter.description: Specifies the arbitration scheme

parameter.name: /timing_parameters/arbitration_delay
parameter.description: Number of cycles taken by the interconnect for performing arbitration. This delay specifies the number of cycles which an incoming request will have to wait to qualify for arbitration

parameter.name: /advanced/num_resources_per_target
parameter.description: Specifies the number of arbitration resources to be associated with a target

parameter.name: /advanced/default_slave_behaviour
parameter.description: Specifies the behaviour of the default slave

parameter.description: Set the clock domain for this port
